  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that the single ASTM F1717 standard configuration represents the sole regulatory use scenario. Validation metrics satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds for all three QoIs. The bench test dataset vintage (2025-10-14) predates the model mesh revision date (2025-11-03) by approximately three weeks; the credibility team determined the revision addressed only element aspect-ratio warnings with no change to material parameters, boundary conditions, or QoI extraction logic, and therefore judged the dataset to remain valid without formal re-validation. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
